main event: Ensign Leonard H. Webster, USN, reported a sighting of a saucer-like object over Washington D.C. on 15 May 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as goldish-orange and was observed for about 10-15 seconds., The sighting involved four observers, ensuring multiple confirmations of the event., The object did not have any appearance of exhaust and was traveling extremely fast., They believed it was not a balloon or any known aircraft due to its speed and maneuvers., The object vanished from sight while still 20-30 degrees above the horizon.
witness description: Ensigns and a civilian employee who resided in Georgetown area of Washington.
